int  lab_id,
int  offset,
void *  rsp_ptr,
int  rsp_size 
)

IOBDMA read operation by providing LAB identifier This will send IOBDMA read request with LAB (transaction ID) and receive response data for the request that was sent earlier.

Parameters:
lap_num - lap number (0 or 1)
lab_id - LAB (transaction ID >= 0) (which is received by cvmx_lap_send_lmtdma_ito() call)
offset - Beginning word number from IOBDMA response buffer (default value 0)
rsp_ptr - Response buffer pointer
rsp_size - Response buffer size (should be more than expected response size)
Returns:
size of Response (>=0) on success else negative (-1) for error
